The broadcast of the final follows an agreement between SABC and SuperSport. It will be broadcast live on SABC 2 on Saturday at 11h00. According to the agreement, SABC 2 will also broadcast the match for the third place playoff between New Zealand and Wales on November 1, at 11h00. SABC’s Group Chief Executive Officer, Madoda Mxakwe, says the public broadcaster is excited to be able to bring this historic game to the nation. “The SABC is excited to be able to bring this historic game to the nation, as the public broadcaster recognises the role it plays in social cohesion, nation building and promoting sports of national interest.” Mxakwe further says the SABC remains committed to entering into commercially viable agreements. “We remain committed to entering into commercially viable agreements and we support and wish the Springboks well as they pursue a place in history.”

